PURPORTBy this offering of obeisances, Arjuna indicates that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is worshipable by everyone. He is all-pervading, and He is the Soul of every soul. Arjuna is addressing K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as mah\xe2\x88\x92tm\xe2\x88\x92, which means that He is most magnanimous and unlimited. Ananta indicates that there is nothing which is not covered by the \ninfluence and energy of the Supreme Lord, and deve\xe2\x80\x9ca means that He is the controller of all demigods and is above them all. He is the center of the whole universe. Arjuna also thought that it was fitting that all the perfect living entities and all powerful demigods offer their respectful obeisances unto Him because no one is greater than Him. He especially mentions that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is greater than Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 because Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 is created by Him. Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 is born out of the lotus stem grown from the navel abdomen of Garbhodaka\xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x80\x9d Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au, who '
b'is K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s plenary expansion; therefore Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and Lord \xe2\x80\xa1iva, who is born of Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, and all other demigods must offer their respectful obeisances. Thus the Lord is respected by Lord \xe2\x80\xa1iva and Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and similar other demigods. The word ak\xc5\x92aram is very significant because this material creation is subject to destruction, but the Lord is above this material creation. He is the cause of all causes, and being so, He is superior to all the conditioned souls within this material nature as well as the material cosmic manifestation itself. He is therefore the all-great Supreme.
