PURPORTArjuna is always in confidence with K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa because he is a very dear friend, and as a dear friend is gladdened by his friend\xc3\x95s opulence, Arjuna is very joyful to see that his friend, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, is the Supreme Personality of Godhead and can show such a wonderful universal form. But at the same time, after seeing that universal form, he is afraid that he has committed so many offenses to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa out of his unalloyed friendship. Thus his mind is disturbed out of fear, although he had no reason to fear. Arjuna therefore is asking K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa to show His N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa form because He can assume any form. This universal form is \nmaterial and temporary, as the material world is temporary. But in the Vaiku\xe2\x80\x9a\xc4\xb1ha planets He has His transcendental form with four hands as N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa. There are innumerable planets in the spiritual sky, and in each of them K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is present by His plenary manifestations of different names. Thus Arjuna desired to see one of the forms manifest in the Vaiku\xe2\x80\x9a\xc4\xb1ha planets. Of course in each Vaiku\xe2\x80\x9a\xc4\xb1ha planet the form of N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa is four-handed, and the four hands hold different symbols, the conchshell, mace, lotus and disc. \nAccording to the different hands these four things are held in, the N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aas '
b'are named. All of these forms are one and the same to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa; therefore Arjuna requests to see His four-handed feature.
