TRANSLATION
The Blessed Lord said: My dear Arjuna, the form which you are now seeing is very difficult to behold. Even the demigods are ever seeking the opportunity to \nsee this form which is so dear.
PURPORTIn the forty-eighth verse of this chapter Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa concluded revealing His universal form and informed Arjuna that this form is not possible to be seen by so many activities, sacrifices, etc. Now here the word sudurdar\xe2\x80\x9cam is used, indicating that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s two-handed form is still more confidential. One may be able to see the universal form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa by adding a little tinge of devotional service to various activities like penance, Vedic study and philosophical speculation, etc. It may be possible, but without a tinge of bhakti, one cannot see; that has already been explained. Still, beyond that universal \nform, the form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as a two-handed man is still more difficult to see, even for demigods like Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and Lord \xe2\x80\xa1iva. They desire to see Him, and we have \nevidences in the \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam that when He was supposed to be in the womb of His mother, Devak\xe2\x80\x9d, all the demigods from heaven came to see the marvel of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. They even waited to see Him. A foolish person may deride Him, but that is an ordinary person. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is actually desired to be seen by demigods like Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1iva in His two-armed form.In Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 it is also confirmed that He is not visible to the foolish persons who deride Him. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s body, as confirmed by Brahm\xe2\x88\x92-sa\xe2\x80\xb9hit\xe2\x88\x92 and '
b'confirmed by Himself in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, is completely spiritual and full of bliss and eternality. His body is never like a material body. But for some who make a study of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa by reading Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 or similar Vedic scriptures, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is a problem. For one using a material process, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is considered to be a great historical personality and very learned philosopher. But He isn\xc3\x95t an ordinary man. But some think that even though He was so powerful, He had to accept a material body. Ultimately they think that the Absolute Truth is impersonal; therefore they think that from His impersonal feature He assumed a personal \nfeature attached to material nature. This is a materialistic calculation of the Supreme Lord. Another calculation is speculative. Those who are in search of knowledge also speculate on K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and consider Him to be less important than the universal form of the Supreme. Thus some think that the universal form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa which was manifested to Arjuna is more important than His personal form. According to them, the personal form of the Supreme is something imaginary. They believe that in the ultimate issue, the Absolute Truth is not a \nperson. But the transcendental process is described in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, Chapter Two: to hear about K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa from authorities. That is the actual Vedic process, \nand those who are actually in the Vedic line hear about K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa from authority, and by repeated hearing about Him, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa becomes dear. As we have several times discussed, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is covered by His yoga-m\xe2\x88\x92y\xe2\x88\x92 potency. He is not to be seen or revealed to anyone and everyone. Only by one to whom He reveals Himself can He be seen. This is confirmed in Vedic literature; for one who is a \nsurrendered soul, the Absolute Truth can actually be understood. The transcendentalist, by continuous K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness and by devotional service to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, can have his spiritual eyes opened and can see K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa by revelation. Such a revelation is not possible even for the demigods; therefore it is difficult even for the demigods to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, and the advanced demigods are always in hope of seeing K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in His two-handed form. The conclusion is that although to see the universal form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is very, very \ndifficult and not possible for anyone and everyone, it is still more difficult to understand His personal form as \xe2\x80\xa1y\xe2\x88\x92masundara.
