The form which you are seeing with your transcendental eyes cannot be understood simply by studying the Vedas, nor by undergoing serious penances, \nnor by charity, nor by worship. It is not by these means that one can see Me as I am.
PURPORTK\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa first appeared before His parents Devak\xe2\x80\x9d and Vasudeva in a four-handed form, and then He transformed Himself into the two-handed form. This mystery is very difficult to understand for those who are atheists or who are devoid of devotional service. For scholars who have simply studied Vedic literature by way of speculation or out of mere academic interest, K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is not easy to understand. Nor is He to he understood by persons who officially go to the temple to offer worship. They make their visit, but they cannot understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as He is. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa can be understood only through the path of devotional service, as explained by K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa Himself in the next verse.
