TRANSLATION
My dear Arjuna, only by undivided devotional service can I be understood as I am, standing before you, and can thus be seen directly. Only in this way can you enter into the mysteries of My understanding.
PURPORTK\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa can be understood only by the process of undivided devotional service. He explicitly explains this in this verse so unauthorized commentators, who try to understand Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 by the speculative process, will know that they are simply wasting their time. No one can understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa or how He \ncame from parents in a four-handed form and at once changed Himself into a two-handed form. It is clearly stated here that no one can see Him. Those who, however, are very experienced students of Vedic literature can learn about Him from the Vedic literature in so many ways. There are so many rules and regulations, and if one at all wants to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, he must follow the regulative principles described in the authoritative literature. One can perform penance in accordance with those principles. As far as charity is \nconcerned, it is plain that charity should be given to the devotees of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa who are engaged in His devotional service to spread the K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa philosophy or K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness throughout the world. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness is a the most munificent man of charity because love of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, which is very difficult to achieve, was distributed freely by Him. And if one worships as prescribed in the temple (in the temples in India there is always some statue, '
b'usually of Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au or K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa), that is a chance to progress. For the beginners in devotional service to the Lord, temple worship is very essential, and this is confirmed in the Vedic literature.One who has unflinching devotion for the Supreme Lord and is directed by the spiritual master can see the Supreme Personality of Godhead by revelation. For one who does not take personal training under the guidance of a bona fide spiritual master, it is impossible to even begin to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. The word tu is specifically used here to indicate that no other process can be \nused, can be recommended, or can be successful in understanding K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa.The personal forms of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, the two-handed form and the four-handed, are completely different from the temporary universal form shown to Arjuna. The four-handed form is N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa, and the two-handed form is K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa; they are eternal and transcendental, whereas the universal form exhibited to Arjuna is temporary. The very word sudurdar\xe2\x80\x9cam, meaning difficult to see, suggests that no one saw that universal form. It also suggests that amongst the devotees \nthere was no necessity of showing it. That form was exhibited by K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa at the request of Arjuna because in the future, when one represents himself as an incarnation of God, people can ask to see his universal form.K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa changes from the universal form to the four-handed form of N\xe2\x88\x92r\xe2\x88\x92ya\xe2\x80\x9aa and then to His own natural form of two hands. This indicates that the four-handed forms and other forms mentioned in Vedic literature are all emanations of the original two-handed K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. He is the origin of all \nemanations. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is distinct even from these forms, not to speak of the impersonal conception. As far as the four-handed forms of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa are concerned, it is stated clearly that even the most identical four-handed form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa (which is known as Mah\xe2\x88\x92-Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au, who is lying on the cosmic ocean and from whose breathing so many innumerable universes are passing out and entering) is also an expansion of the Supreme Lord. Therefore one should conclusively worship the personal form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as the Supreme Personality of \nGodhead who is eternity, bliss and knowledge. He is the source of all forms of Vi\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9au, He is the source of all forms of incarnation, and He is the original Supreme Personality, as confirmed in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92.In the Vedic literature it is stated that the Supreme Absolute Truth is a person. His name is K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, and He sometimes descends on this earth. Similarly, in \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam there is a description of all kinds of '
b'incarnations of the Supreme Personality of Godhead, and there it is said that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is not an incarnation of God but is the original Supreme Personality of Godhead Himself. K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aas tu bhagav\xe2\x88\x92n svayam. Similarly, in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 the Lord says, matta\xc5\xa1 parataram n\xe2\x88\x92ny\xe2\x88\x92t: \xc3\x92There is nothing superior to My form as the Personality of Godhead K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa.\xc3\x93 He also says elsewhere in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, aham \xe2\x88\x92dir hi dev\xe2\x88\x92n\xe2\x88\x92m: \xc3\x92I am the origin of all the demigods.\xc3\x93 And after understanding Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 from K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, Arjuna also confirms this in the following words: para\xe2\x80\xb9 brahma para\xe2\x80\xb9 dh\xe2\x88\x92ma pavitra\xe2\x80\xb9 parama\xe2\x80\xb9 bhav\xe2\x88\x92n: \xc3\x92I \nnow fully understand that You are the Supreme Personality of Godhead, the Absolute Truth, and that You are the refuge of everything.\xc3\x93 Therefore the universal form which K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa showed to Arjuna is not the original form of God. The original is the K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa form. The universal form, with its thousands and thousands of heads and hands, is manifest just to draw the attention of those who have no love for God. It is not God\xc3\x95s original form.The universal form is not attractive for pure devotees, who are in love with \nthe Lord in different transcendental relationships. The Supreme Godhead exchanges transcendental love in His original form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. Therefore to Arjuna, who was so intimately related with K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa in friendship, this form of the universal manifestation was not pleasing; rather, it was fearful. Arjuna, who is a constant companion of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s, must have had transcendental eyes; he was not an ordinary man. Therefore he was not captivated by the universal form. This form may seem wonderful to persons who are involved in elevating \nthemselves by fruitive activities, but to persons who are engaged in devotional service, the two-handed form of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the most dear.
